   <title class="- topic/title " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\ntb\trident_ntb_ntep_host_driver.xml" xtrc="title:1;14:26">NTB Host Driver</title>
   <body class="- topic/body " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\ntb\trident_ntb_ntep_host_driver.xml" xtrc="body:1;17:24">
      <p audience="MSCCInternal" class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\ntb\trident_ntb_ntep_host_driver.xml" xtrc="p:1;21:21">Switchtec NTB is supported through the Switchtec open source driver framework which is pre-compiled into Linux Kernels 4.11 and newer. It can also be downloaded from github here: <xref href="https://github.com/Microsemi/switchtec-kernel" scope="external" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\ntb\trident_ntb_ntep_host_driver.xml" xtrc="xref:1;25:30"><?ditaot usertext?> https://github.com/Microsemi/switchtec-kernel</xref>.</p>
      <p audience="MSCCInternal" class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\ntb\trident_ntb_ntep_host_driver.xml" xtrc="p:2;29:21">Switchtec NTB driver is developed in a sandbox in the short-term before merging into the main open repositories.</p>
      <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\ntb\trident_ntb_ntep_host_driver.xml" xtrc="p:3;32:21">This driver supports a dual host configuration with NTB and can be extended to support more than two hosts.</p>
      <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\ntb\trident_ntb_ntep_host_driver.xml" xtrc="p:4;35:21">The driver requires the following configuration settings:</p>
      <ul class="- topic/ul " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\ntb\trident_ntb_ntep_host_driver.xml" xtrc="ul:1;38:23">
         <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\ntb\trident_ntb_ntep_host_driver.xml" xtrc="li:1;41:26">
            <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\ntb\trident_ntb_ntep_host_driver.xml" xtrc="p:5;44:27"> Both NT partitions must be able to access each other's GAS spaces. This can be set in the configuration file permission settings</p>
         </li>
         <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\ntb\trident_ntb_ntep_host_driver.xml" xtrc="li:2;48:26">
            <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\ntb\trident_ntb_ntep_host_driver.xml" xtrc="p:6;51:27"> The bits in the GAS Access Vector under Management Settings must be set to support this</p>
         </li>
         <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\ntb\trident_ntb_ntep_host_driver.xml" xtrc="li:3;55:26">
            <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\ntb\trident_ntb_ntep_host_driver.xml" xtrc="p:7;58:27"> Kernel configuration MUST include support for NTB (CONFIG_NTB needs to be set)</p>
         </li>
         <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\ntb\trident_ntb_ntep_host_driver.xml" xtrc="li:4;62:26">
            <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\ntb\trident_ntb_ntep_host_driver.xml" xtrc="p:8;65:27"> NT EP BAR 2 will be dynamically configured as a Direct Window (there is no need to configure the direct windows in the switch configuration file)</p>
         </li>
         <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\ntb\trident_ntb_ntep_host_driver.xml" xtrc="li:5;69:26">
            <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\ntb\trident_ntb_ntep_host_driver.xml" xtrc="p:9;72:27">Please refer to Documentation/ntb.txt in Linux source tree for an overall understanding of the Linux NTB stack. ntb_hw_switchtec works as an NTB Hardware Driver in this stack</p>
         </li>
      </ul>
